          ## Full Stack Anxiety
          A perfect compliment to Alice‚Äôs talk, #{link_to 'Joel Califa', 'https://twitter.com/notdetails', target: '_blank'} took to the stage te give an inspiring talk on the anxiety many of us in this industry feel...

          ... and also to take a group selfie.

  = partial("photoessays/components/photo_right", locals: {slug: current_page.data.slug, 'photo': 'joel_selfie', 'caption': 'Joel gets a group selfie with the audience' })

  .Content_row
    .Content_main
      .Article_content
        :markdown
          Joel‚Äôs talk particularly resonated with me. There‚Äôs so much to learn in our industry that it can sometimes feel overwhelming and exhausting ‚Äî trying to keep up with everything ‚Äî or even just knowing what to focus on learning.

          There‚Äôs more opportunities than ever in our industry, but there‚Äôs also more expectations too. Designers 15 years ago who could code their designs were a bit of a rarity. Now, it‚Äôs almost a requirement.

          And it‚Äôs not just that. Designers these days are expected to be experienced with prototyping, user experience research, and more. And with the landscape in modern web development, developers don‚Äôt have it any easier.

          One of the key takeaways for me was to take more time to be more thoughtful and intention with what you actually want to learn, and to prioritise general, fundamental skills over trends and fashions.

          > Your life in its entirety deserves the level of care you put into your projects. So put some time in... and design it.

