          ## Designing Design Systems

          Next, #{link_to 'Jina Bolton', 'https://twitter.com/jina', target: '_blank'} took to the stage to talk about design systems, and her experience working with design systems at Salesforce.

  = partial("photoessays/components/photo_right", locals: {slug: current_page.data.slug, 'photo': 'jina', 'caption': '' })

  .Content_row
    .Content_main
      .Article_content
        :markdown
          As Jina pointed out, design systems can mean a lot of things to different people ‚Äî from branding style guides and moodboards, to far more thorough component libraries. So nailing down a proper definition can be hard, it can be any of those things, depending on the situation. Above all else, Design systems help to bring clarity and consistency to applications and websites.

          But in order to bring these benefits, they must not be neglected. Jina outlined a number of different methodologies for managing design systems, and stressed the importance of buy-in from stakeholders and all parties for design systems to be used to their full advantage.

          Design systems is a subject I‚Äôm very interested in, and Jina‚Äôs talk proved to be an insightful and inspirational start.

